   MANY
matriculants received their results on Friday, January 20. But not all
of them have passed. The
Department of Basic Education says those who didn't make it, have until 15
March to apply for rewriting their matric exams. The
department's spokesman, Elijah Mhlanga said 15 March is the date where
applications will be closed for those who want to improve their marks on the
results. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments He said
after the deadline, no late applications will be accepted as the process is
regulated. Those
wanting to rewrite are urged to start applying as soon as they get their
results.